releaseNotes:
# Xamarin Insights client release, version 1.8.0 

This release is mostly bug fixes but has some requested changes, most of all, *Unified support!* In addition we increased the precision of all our events which should help the out of order issues some people have been seeing. 

aside from minor api overload changes, we have introduced a new call. ```Xamarin.Insights.Save();``` - Please note that this is not intended for regular Insights use, but if you happen to disable Insights automatic exception reporting, you should make sure to call this after all your Insights calls in your own unhandled exception handler. 

## Stats for milestone [1.8.0] 

### Fixed Issues: 

* #1092 - Throw when empty api key is passed to Insights.Initialize() 
* #1073 - Max Iteration Reached message breaks json 
* #1028 - mono platform crash in deviceinfo lookup 
* #1027 - Send Identifier with Trackevents and Reports 
* #1025 - Use millisecond timestamps for 1.8.0 
* #1005 - X-Recurssion-Limit-Reached is not string enclosed 
* #988 - Android crash in deviceID when app is crashing 
* #983 - protect against too many open files on android 
* #981 - Make android stability a bit higher by protecting around registering and unregistering network change recievers 
* #976 - Android client calls log in plat servcies init which causes a cyclic issue with platform services null checking 
* #970 - report needs a block variant or switch 
* #948 - Track/tracktime should provide a dictionaryless api 
* #947 - TrackTime handles should allow you to add items to the dictionary that we are sending 
* #896 - locks too early 
* #807 - Make a Xamarin.Insights component for Rdio and friends 
* #469 - Support unified api
